# AGENTS.md — {{project}}

Short house rules for AI coding assistants working in this repo.

## Local checks

Run before considering work complete:

```bash
./scripts/check.sh          # or language-equivalent local gate
```

If `scripts/check.sh` is missing, use standard commands for the stack
(`cargo test`, `uv run pytest`, `ruff`, etc.).

## PR flow (protect main / dev)

1. Create a feature or chore branch (never commit directly to `main`)
2. Make changes; keep diffs small
3. Open PR → **`dev`** first (when the repo uses a dev trunk)
4. Promote `dev` → `main` when ready for release

### Issue linking tiers

| Target branch | Issue keywords |
|---------------|----------------|
| `dev` / feature | **`Refs #n`** / `Related to #n` only — issues stay open |
| `main` | **`Closes #n`** / **`Fixes #n`** for completed work |

Epics close only when the delivery PR to `main` includes `Closes #<epic>`.

## Safety

- No secrets, tokens, or credentials in commits, logs, or issue bodies
- Do **not** request automatic Copilot code review
- Prefer cited evidence over assumptions when a corpus index (Tero) is available

